11/30/2023,748.1335 - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,02/02/2024,02/02/2024,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium Low,No,During the investigation it was found that a child's service plan was not completed timely.,"Upon Admission into Wholeness Haven RTC. Each youth will receive a Preliminary 
Service Plan within 72 hours. Once A child has been in the care of Wholeness Haven for 30 days, 
the Treatment Director will send out the Invite Email for the Service Plan meeting 2 weeks in 
advance of the meeting. As part of the Service Planning process, the Treatment Director will also 
schedule the next Service Plan meeting notification by entering the respective dates into our data 
base system called CaseBook. Once entered into the system, it will be recorded under the 
Compliance Date tab. Once properly entered, CaseBook will generate an alert prior to the next
notification due date. Once the Service Plan has been completed, the date of completion will be 
entered as well as the Service Plan effective date. Once the initial Service Plan process is complete 
the, date of the next meeting request will be entered into CaseBook, as well as the next Service 
Plan review date. CaseBook will automatically record this information in the compliance date
section and send out alerts prior to the dates as will be indicated by highlighting the respective 
section in red. Wholeness Haven Administration will routinely review all information as it relates 
to Service Planning Compliance and coordination to ensure deadlines are adhered to."
10/02/2023,748.1349(a)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/04/2023,12/04/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Low,Yes,A child did not receive a copy of their initial service plan.,"Upon completion of the Single Child Plan of Service, a copy will be sent to the Managing conservator (Caseworker) for their signature and the request will be documented in the youths file. The Therapist, and or case manager will review the Single Child Plan of Service with the youth and have the youth sign the signature page. In the event a youth refuses to sign, respective staff will note that on the signature line. Subsequent attempts will be made to get the youth to sign the Service Plan. In the event of subsequent refusals, documentation of each attempt will be placed in the youths file as well as forwarded to the youths Managing Conservator (caseworker). If the Service Plan is discussed with the youth and the youth refuses to sign, documentation of the discussion will be placed in the youths file as well as forwarded to the youths Managing Conservator (caseworker). The youths Service Plan will include documentation of the plan having been shared with the youth and the youth's parents or Managing Conservator and the youth response to service to date."
