06/28/2023,748.2003(b)(5) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/28/2023,08/27/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Review of kids in care medication administration records revealed medications were not administered as prescribed.,"We have added several layers of redundancy to our medication audit and review system to ensure optimal quality control. The facility administrator and the facility executive director audit the medication daily with each on alternate days. The facility administration also audits the medication daily before and after the medication has been administered. The facility administration also periodically supervises the medication administration process. The facility Staff Supervisor along with either the facility executive director or the facility administrator oversees the bi-weekly psychiatric medication review to ensure optimal accuracy in interpretation and communication of all pertinent information concerning the youths medication. The accurate information, as well as updated orders, if applicable, is then immediately disseminated to all staff. Due to possible frequent hospitalizations, the psychiatrist is also provided with the current status of the youths medication, its effect, the dosage and count as an added layer of quality control. If at any time a discrepancy is discovered, a plan of action will be put in place to address the specific circumstances and to prevent reoccurrence."
